I'm baaaaaaack!! I took about 6 days off... after my last midterm I was d r a i n e d. Emotionally, physically, and mentally. The last practice (Day 25) I pushed myself a little too far and ended up incredibly sore in the oops-is-this-an-injury kind of way. I had only intended to take 1-2 days off for my body to recover but it ended up being a full on total body/mind rest with 0 studying and 0 physical activity... except for when it was 21c here and I walked down to and swam in the ocean for the first time this year... (I get off topic incredibly easily). Anyway, today I woke up with a head cold. I thought I was going to end up taking another day off but after the advil cold and sinus kicked in this evening I felt restless and ready to get back into it. I took my mat outside even though it was raining ever so slightly and I did this practice in the fading light of this spring evening, with mother nature and all her plant children coming to life around me. WOW. The STRENGTH I felt in my body surprised me! I effortlessly got my heels down in downward dog, and even though I felt my breath speed up and my heart rate increase, I felt the practice was easy & manageable. I surprised and amazed myself and again I am so incredibly grateful for this channel <3 Thank you, Adriene!!

Adriene, I love hearing you say that moderation is empowerment. I injured my wrist and tried to power through, making my injury worse. It also caused more pain on the other side of my body, which was compensating for the weakness on the opposite side of my body. Since then, I've been moderating the down dog, plank and other poses that require using my wrist, by going down on my elbows, or using puppy pose in place of down dog. Moderating has provided more strength and power in other areas of my body. I love finding what feels good and I thank you for your encouragement to do so! Namaste <3
